        "content": "<p>Here is the screenshot of modal that pops-up when web public visitor is trying to access something like  PMs which is not allowed.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/2/e7/xg9hdrgbbcx7FXVyxBwjm3pL/Screenshot-2021-05-25-at-6.22.17-PM.png\">Screenshot-2021-05-25-at-6.22.17-PM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/2/e7/xg9hdrgbbcx7FXVyxBwjm3pL/Screenshot-2021-05-25-at-6.22.17-PM.png\" title=\"Screenshot-2021-05-25-at-6.22.17-PM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/2/e7/xg9hdrgbbcx7FXVyxBwjm3pL/Screenshot-2021-05-25-at-6.22.17-PM.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 1187937,
        "sender_full_name": "Aman (amanagr)",
        "timestamp": 1621947244
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What do you guys think of the design?</p>",
        "id": 1187938,
        "sender_full_name": "Aman (amanagr)",
        "timestamp": 1621947262
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The blue and white colour toggles when you hover over it.</p>",
        "id": 1187939,
        "sender_full_name": "Aman (amanagr)",
        "timestamp": 1621947316
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would change the label at the top to \"Login required\" -- we don't want to suggest that they need special access, just that they need to create an account.</p>",
        "id": 1188055,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1621956312
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think we also want the \"Log in\" button to be a happy-path button, and probably to offer a \"Sign up\" button as well, since a common situation will be that folks using this feature don't have accounts.</p>",
        "id": 1188058,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1621956388
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, makes sense.</p>",
        "id": 1188097,
        "sender_full_name": "Aman (amanagr)",
        "timestamp": 1621961177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would probably have it say something like:</p>\n<p><code>Because you are not logged in, you can only view messages in [Web public streams](link).</code></p>",
        "id": 1188256,
        "sender_full_name": "Alya Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1621969586
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, that works for me.</p>",
        "id": 1188314,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1621972028
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We might want another sentence to make clear you also can't change anything, but it's kinda obvious, so I'd skip that for just getting something in that we can start merging the hooks to call.</p>",
        "id": 1188315,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Abbott",
        "timestamp": 1621972049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay.</p>",
